<subSubSection id="C319654DFFF9FF90FEB1FD9CFB795465" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF9FF90FEB1FD9CFB795465" blockId="12.[192,1441,528,768]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF9FF90FEB1FD9CFE5E552A" box="[256,403,565,591]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
: Valle de 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF9FF90FE4CFD9CFD185535" box="[509,725,565,592]" country="Colombia" name="Cauca" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Cauca Department</collectingRegion>
, Santiago de Cali; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF9FF90FC12FD9CFB94552A" box="[931,1113,565,592]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" value="2021-01-16">16 January 2021</date>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF9FF90FBD5FD9FFBBA5535" box="[1124,1143,566,592]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Vieda. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF9FF90FEAFFDF1FE0A5516" authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1878" box="[286,455,600,627]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anyphaenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp grasped the immobilized ghost spider’s spinnerets with her mandibles while straddling it venter to venter. The left hindleg and right hind-, third and second legs were amputated at the coxa-trochanter joints (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF9FF90FD7BFD37FC8355DC" author="Vieda V." box="[714,846,670,697]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" refId="ref27258" refString="Vieda V. 2021. Mud-nesting Spider Wasps (Tribe Ageniellini). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 68163274. (Last accessed 19 January 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Vieda 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF9FF90FB87FD36FB5655DD" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1078,1179,670,697]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF9FF90FB87FD36FB5655DD" box="[1078,1179,670,697]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">A. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported from Colombia by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF9FF90FEBAFD68FE6D55B9" author="Banks N." box="[267,416,705,732]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="311 - 525" refId="ref21154" refString="Banks N. 1946. Studies of South American Psammocharidae. Part I. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College 96: 311 - 525." type="journal article" year="1946">Banks (1946)</bibRefCitation>
and represented in our host record may not be the same 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF9FF90FB99FD6BFAE355B9" authority="(Smith, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1064,1326,705,732]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF9FF90FB99FD6BFB4055BE" box="[1064,1165,705,732]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">A. viridis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF9FF90FB2AFD68FAEB55B9" author="Smith F." box="[1179,1318,705,732]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="263 - 270" refId="ref26850" refString="Smith F. 1864. Descriptions of new species of Brazilian Pompilidae. Journal of Entomology 2: 263 - 270." type="journal article" year="1864">Smith, 1864</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
originally described from São Paulo, Brazil, as discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF9FF90FD59FD4CFCB35465" author="Banks N." box="[744,894,741,768]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="311 - 525" refId="ref21154" refString="Banks N. 1946. Studies of South American Psammocharidae. Part I. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College 96: 311 - 525." type="journal article" year="1946">Banks (1946)</bibRefCitation>
. (Waichert 2021 pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
